iPads for Education

District students are receiving their iPads this week in school. The devices will go home with students every evening so they can continue to access school work on remote days.

We are excited to offer this program to our students, staff, and families. We understand it is new and there will be questions about the devices and programs. To help, a new district web site with resources for all students is now accessible under the channel "Students and Families" and "Digital Learning".

https://www.swasd.org/students-and-families/digital-learning/

post_text:
Health Screenings Before School

We are so excited to have students and teachers back in school this week. To help ensure all students and staff are safe and can remain in school, please continue to conduct a health assessment before leaving for school each morning using the magnet provided.

If your child has one (1) symptom from the Group A list or if they have two (2) symptoms from the Group B list, or you are taking fever reducing medicine, please stay home AND email our school district nurse at covid19@swasd.org.

See you tomorrow!

post_text:
Federal Assistance for Families

The federal Families First Corona-virus Response Act of 2020 will provide money to eligible families for school meals missed while school was closed.

The program will provide $5.70 per day per school age child who qualifies for free or reduced price meals. If your child was already receiving free / reduced meals before school closed, no further action is required.

If you have experienced a change in family income, you may now qualify and may receive this financial benefit.

Go to My School Café at https://www.schoolcafe.com/SouthWillamsportASD. Create an account if you do not have one and submit a meal application.

post_text:
Food Backpack Program Continues

Each Wednesday, with the assistance of Messiah Lutheran Church, the district continues to provide meals to children in need through the school food backpack program. Enrollment is open to any SWASD student. Simply email your child’s building principal so we are sure to have enough bags each week. No forms, no signatures. Just a simple email.

This program purchases food using local donations directly form the Central PA Food Bank at significantly reduced costs. If you would like to make a donation to help us continue to buy food, follow the link below. In the comment section type “SWASD Food Backpack Program”

https://www.centralpafoodbank.org/campaigns/covid19-3/

Attention Students and Families

The South Williamsport Area School District is deeply concerned about the education of students during this sudden closure of school. We hope it is short. In the meantime, we want them to Keep Looking and Keep Learning. With the help of the staff, we will share information on free web resources to help your student stay engaged with their education. These are intended for any student and we hope you can use them as an opportunity to enjoy a Mountie Learning Moment with your child! Check back regularly for new posts!

Today's Mountie Learning Moment is from Brain Pop. Your student knows this program and now they are offering it to families for free while schools are closed. Check it out!

www.brainpop.com

post_text:
Schools Closed: March 16 - March 27

As I am sure you have heard by now, the Governor closed all schools in the Commonwealth for 10 business days beginning Monday. While closed, all school activities, on or off campus, are also cancelled effective today through Sunday, March 29. While closed the district will complete a deep cleaning of all district facilities.

Families and staff will be notified by phone and email of important updates including reopening of school, extensions to the closure, or other relevant information. Information will also be posted on the district web site.

Your patience is appreciated as the district responds to the Governor’s directives and supports him to manage the spread of COVID-19 in the Commonwealth. We will provide regular updates on the status of school and school activities as information is available.

Read Across America

Central students celebrated Read Across America this week with a lot of great activities. Today it all culminated with the faculty talent show and Dr. Loomis getting slimed. Such a fun end of the week activity. Congratulations to all the students and faculty for working hard to make it such a success for all students. Mrs. Loiselle’s 2nd grade classroom was the grand prize winner for reading the most minutes this week with over 12,000 minutes. They were the lucky class that got to slim Dr. Loomis.

Elementary Tiny-THON - $2212

This past Friday Night the Elementary Tiny-THON was held in the high school auxiliary gym. 110 elementary students participated, and 22 high school students showed up to help with the festivities. The elementary students raised $2212 for Four Diamonds. What an outstanding job by all our elementary students that participated and our high school students that helped make this night such a great success.

The high school Mini-THON is this Friday and Saturday from 7pm - 7am. The community is invited on Friday from 7pm - 10pm.

Thank you to everyone that has made this such a great success for so many years.

LEO Club Raising Money for Operation Smile

Leo Club is raising funds to pay for a cleft palate or cleft lip surgery with Operation Smile. Operation Smile is an international non-profit that provides this surgery to children around the world.

You can help too!
